  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs an alpha user, I want to use Mainnet so that I can test with real ETH and use real Dapps.\r\n\r\nAs a Status developer, I want to get Mainnet feedback so that I can improve the app.\r\n\r\nAs a dapp developer, I want to test my Dapp on Mainnet so that I can verify it works.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Status app is in alpha for testing, development, and feedback, but usage is limited because users are limited to Testnet and can't test real Dapps or do transactions with real ETH.  Over the last few weeks there have been only several recorded transactions but in comparison, there have been thousands of messages sent. Adding mainnet as a network option will allow testing for users acquainted with the risks and get valuable feedback.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nA user goes to Profile, taps Advanced, taps Network, then taps Mainnet. A warning message with opt-in is displayed. Confirming will switch to Mainnet.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nA user goes to Profile, taps Advanced, taps Network, but Mainnet is not an option.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n- Add Mainnet as a [non-default] option to Alpha release builds\r\n- Show a warning message\r\n\r\nDetails:\r\n- [Design: WIP prototype of the flow showing the steps to enable](https://invis.io/A5H52F12NBK)\r\n- [Copy: WIP copy of the opt-in warning alert](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1UfNy8o5clvvRppGbF0aeMx2p1ce-YZsJ7PXcsfXGfqo/edit?usp=sharing)\r\n\r\n\r\nThis solution is only needed until Beta when Mainnet will be the default network.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nThis issue is WIP until any associated security or UX concerns can be investigated.\r\n\r\nRelated issues to research:\r\n- Encrypt realm https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/3798 & PR https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/3829 \r\n- Mixpanel ID's https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4006 & PR https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/4068\r\n\r\ncc @goranjovic @adambabik ",
